# SPU-13 Null Hysteresis Constraints: iCeSugar (iCE40UP5K)
# v3.1.31 "Vortex Routing"
# Objective: Physical mapping for Laminar Silence and Zero-Jitter entry.

# --- 1. Resonant Clock Entry (Chiral Vortex) ---
# Pin 35 is the Global Clock input. We map it here to ensure the Sierpinski
# clock tree has a geometrically centered root.
set_io clk_resonant 35

# --- 2. Janus-Gate Differential Output ---
# These pins are physically adjacent on the PMOD connector, allowing for
# twisted-pair routing to external bio-monitors.
# By driving them differentially (one +Janus, one -Janus), we cancel electromagnetic emissions.
set_io janus_pos 46
set_io janus_neg 47

# --- 3. Manifold Status Indicators (Spectral Balance) ---
# The RGB LED is used to visualize the internal rotation state.
# Red = Axis A (Invariant), Green = Axis B/C/D (Orbit), Blue = Phase Lock.
set_io led_red   39
set_io led_green 40
set_io led_blue  41

# --- 4. Command & Control (Surd-Bridge) ---
# The UART interface allows the Rust Surd-Converter to drive the core.
# Mapped to the dedicated FTDI pins for minimal latency.
set_io uart_tx 10
set_io uart_rx 9

# --- 5. Fractal Logic Placement Hints ---
# While PCF cannot force internal routing, these IO placements encourage
# the place-and-route tool to utilize the central logic blocks, keeping
# the signal path symmetrical.
